data.name: groupBoxQlty.ToolTip
data.value: YouTube uses a technology called Dynamic Adaptive Streaming over HTTP (DASH), also known as MPEG-DASH, to stream the videos. The maximum quality of non-DASH video available is 720p. Inorder to download DASH videos, you need the ffmpeg library installed in your system. A simple googling will help you install it. DASH video streams are seperated as audio streams and video streams. So YouTube Downloader will first download the video, then the audio, and then use ffmpeg to merge them into one file. So dont panic if the progress bar reaches completion and starts all over again! Just sit tight and relax!
